WEBVTT

00:01.914 --> 00:03.351
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Friends, we last left
Jane and Rafael

00:03.394 --> 00:05.440
dealing with
an unexpected development.

00:05.483 --> 00:07.311
I believe Mateo does have ADHD.

00:07.355 --> 00:08.443
How can we help him?

00:08.486 --> 00:10.140
Well, there are
treatment options

00:10.184 --> 00:11.968
that range from behavior
interventions to medication.

00:12.012 --> 00:14.362
But at least the two of them
were back in a good place.

00:14.405 --> 00:17.234
Not in such a good place?
Our Petra.

00:17.278 --> 00:19.454
See, she was going
to propose to J.R.,

00:19.497 --> 00:22.326
but then J.R. broke up with her and moved to Houston.

00:22.370 --> 00:24.502
But at least Petra had
a shoulder to ugly-cry on.

00:24.546 --> 00:26.939
I was gonna propose.

00:26.983 --> 00:28.550
Also feeling vulnerable?
Xiomara.

00:28.593 --> 00:31.770
See, she was waiting to find out if her chemotherapy worked.

00:31.814 --> 00:34.686
I'm not out of the woods yet,
until after the PET scan.

00:34.730 --> 00:36.993
And so, yeah, everything was
on pause for now,

00:37.037 --> 00:39.300
including her sex life,
unlike Alba,

00:39.343 --> 00:40.475
who just got hitched!

00:40.518 --> 00:42.390
That's right.

00:42.433 --> 00:45.001
Alba and Jorge went
from first base to a home run.

00:45.045 --> 00:47.395
And speaking of home runs,

00:47.438 --> 00:49.353
Rogelio had
a brand-new TV show.

00:49.397 --> 00:52.095
What if our young lead's story
is in present day

00:52.139 --> 00:54.358
and you and River
are living in the future?

00:54.402 --> 00:55.751
On Mars!

00:55.794 --> 00:59.320
We can call it This Is Mars.

00:59.363 --> 01:01.452
I know,
pretty out there, right?

01:01.496 --> 01:03.454
But hey, it's a telenovela.

01:03.498 --> 01:07.458
So let's blast off into ours.

01:07.502 --> 01:10.461
When Jane Gloriana Villanueva
was...

01:10.505 --> 01:12.681
well, actually,
for all of Jane's life,

01:12.724 --> 01:15.727
there was no man of the house,
just three women.

01:15.771 --> 01:17.512
And they didn't need a man,

01:17.555 --> 01:19.470
because they took care
of it all.

01:19.514 --> 01:20.906
Electricity went up.

01:20.950 --> 01:22.343
Mom, remember not to leave

01:22.386 --> 01:23.779
your curling iron
plugged in all day.

01:23.822 --> 01:26.086
My curling iron doesn't use
half as much electricity

01:26.129 --> 01:28.784
as the fans your abuela
keeps running all day.

01:32.657 --> 01:34.137
XIOMARA: There,
no more wobble.

01:34.181 --> 01:36.139
JANE:
Ooh, I like that nail polish.

01:36.183 --> 01:38.054
Thanks. it's called
Breakfast in Red.

01:38.098 --> 01:39.577
I'll loan it to you.

01:41.362 --> 01:43.494
In fact, Jane had never heard

01:43.538 --> 01:47.542
the term "man of the house"
used in real life until...

01:52.112 --> 01:54.157
JORGE:
Mm.

01:57.421 --> 02:00.946
Aww, looks like the man
and woman of the house

02:00.990 --> 02:03.166
are in still
in the honeymoon phase.

02:03.210 --> 02:04.950
So what's on the
agenda today? Huh?

02:04.994 --> 02:07.388
Besides being totally adorable.

02:11.827 --> 02:13.002
JORGE:
Now that our arrangement

02:13.045 --> 02:14.482
is permanent,

02:14.525 --> 02:16.484
I'm taking my things
out of storage.

02:16.527 --> 02:19.051
Oh, great.

02:21.663 --> 02:22.838
Not at all. I'll
do it right now.

02:22.881 --> 02:24.579
Anything for my new step-abuelo.

02:24.622 --> 02:26.058
And maybe you could move some

02:26.102 --> 02:28.583
of your bathroom things
into your room.

02:28.626 --> 02:30.759
All the hair stuff.

02:30.802 --> 02:33.240
Of course.

02:49.560 --> 02:50.387
Hey, uh,

02:50.431 --> 02:52.433
how you feeling?Itchy.

02:52.476 --> 02:54.478
Your sheets are awful.
What thread count are they?

02:54.522 --> 02:56.219
I don't know. They were on sale.

02:56.263 --> 02:57.916
I'll have Temp send you
a set from the hotel.

02:57.960 --> 02:59.091
They're Egyptian cotton.

02:59.135 --> 03:01.224
I...

03:01.268 --> 03:03.618
I meant how
are you feeling about J.R.?

03:03.661 --> 03:05.228
I had a good cry and now
I'm going to move forward.

03:05.272 --> 03:08.188
It's okay to give yourself
some time to wallow.

03:08.231 --> 03:10.015
No, I wallowed last night,
now I'm moving on.

03:10.059 --> 03:11.669
Fresh start.

03:11.713 --> 03:14.106
Ugh. I'm supposed to be
in a meeting right now,

03:14.150 --> 03:15.717
but Temp didn't remind me.

03:15.760 --> 03:17.632
You know what?

03:17.675 --> 03:19.721
Today I'm about fresh starts
all around. She's fired.

03:19.764 --> 03:22.332
Oh, no. Uh... Poor Temp.

03:22.376 --> 03:24.204
When you reward incompetence,
we all lose.

03:24.247 --> 03:26.684
Wait. Uh, I'll walk you out.

03:26.728 --> 03:28.991
I have to get to Rafael's
to talk about...

03:29.034 --> 03:30.645
Mateo! Five more minutes, okay?

03:32.560 --> 03:35.476
So what do you think about
putting him on ADHD medication?

03:35.519 --> 03:38.218
I really don't want
to go to that right away.

03:38.261 --> 03:40.350
Because medication
is a lifelong decision,

03:40.394 --> 03:42.309
and he is so young and I just,

03:42.352 --> 03:44.006
I don't feel comfortable...Jane.

03:44.049 --> 03:46.574
I agree.
You do?

03:46.617 --> 03:49.620
Yeah, 100%. I'm obviously not
anti-medication--

03:49.664 --> 03:52.144
it's really helped a lot with my
depression-- but I'm an adult,

03:52.188 --> 03:54.625
and he's a kid, so we should try
other options first.

03:54.669 --> 03:56.192
Exactly. So let's dive

03:56.236 --> 03:57.976
into behavior modification.Sounds good.

03:58.020 --> 04:01.632
Now hand over whatever ten-step
list I know you've already made.

04:01.676 --> 04:03.678
Actually, it's 15,
with subcategories.

04:03.721 --> 04:04.940
I've been researching and...

04:04.983 --> 04:06.463
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
You know,

04:06.507 --> 04:08.073
I'm the man of this telenovela,

04:08.117 --> 04:10.467
and I say
let's skip the boring stuff.

04:10.511 --> 04:13.688
It all boils down
to three basic headlines...

04:14.993 --> 04:16.691
In other words, "cut the crap."

04:18.736 --> 04:22.523
Uh, sorry, I'm just picturing
Jane working out. Whew.

04:22.566 --> 04:23.567
Okay.

04:26.353 --> 04:28.703
And the most important thing
to remember is

04:28.746 --> 04:30.879
it's not about the days,
it's about the patterns.

04:30.922 --> 04:32.837
That's our mantra.

04:32.881 --> 04:35.144
Look at us, with a mantra.A mantra. And...

04:35.187 --> 04:37.102
a notebook.
Ah.

04:37.146 --> 04:39.104
So we can keep a log
of Mateo's activities.

04:39.148 --> 04:41.324
We need everything to be
as consistent as possible

04:41.368 --> 04:42.891
between our two places

04:42.934 --> 04:44.893
so we can track
Mateo's patterns over time.

04:44.936 --> 04:46.677
Per the mantra.

04:46.721 --> 04:48.200
Remind me of the mantra again?

04:48.244 --> 04:49.332
I'll write it in the notebook.

04:49.376 --> 04:50.507
ROGELIO:
You've got this.

04:50.551 --> 04:52.379
You're killing it, Dina.

04:52.422 --> 04:54.381
Okay, bye.

04:54.424 --> 04:57.209
Dina's been working like a
madwoman to finish the script

04:57.253 --> 04:59.211
for This Is Mars.
She's almost done.

04:59.255 --> 05:01.866
Wow, that was fast.

05:01.910 --> 05:05.566
Yeah. She's turning it in
tonight, yes, she is.

05:05.609 --> 05:10.005
The pilot is brilliant.
Between that and this,

05:10.048 --> 05:12.181
the network has to
give us a pilot order.

05:12.224 --> 05:14.183
That's great, hon.

05:14.226 --> 05:16.968
Hopefully, we'll both
be getting good news soon.

05:17.012 --> 05:19.580
The doctor scheduled
my final PET scan.

05:19.623 --> 05:22.626
In three weeks, we'll find out
if the chemo worked.

05:22.670 --> 05:24.628
Really?

05:24.672 --> 05:26.804
How are you feeling?

05:26.848 --> 05:31.287
I'm nervous,
but I'm trying to stay positive.

05:31.331 --> 05:33.811
I keep picturing all
of the things I'll be able to do

05:33.855 --> 05:35.683
once I know the cancer's gone.

05:35.726 --> 05:40.340
Get back to work,
dance again.

05:40.383 --> 05:43.778
And maybe even get our sex life
back on track before we turn 50.

05:45.083 --> 05:47.042
Well, no matter
what happens,

05:47.085 --> 05:50.088
we're in this together,
and that's the key.

05:51.133 --> 05:52.830
Ah! Abuela!

05:52.874 --> 05:54.005
Hmm?

05:54.049 --> 05:55.877
What happened to the table
by the door?

06:00.882 --> 06:01.970
Don't. I-I want it.

06:19.770 --> 06:21.293
JORGE:
Jane, door!

06:25.863 --> 06:27.256
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Yeah, so there's been

06:27.299 --> 06:29.867
quite a bit of re-Jorganizing
in here.

06:33.654 --> 06:36.178
I've got it, don't worry.

06:37.484 --> 06:39.747
Petra? What's wrong?

06:39.790 --> 06:42.750
Oh, I was cleaning the penthouse

06:42.793 --> 06:46.275
because my idiot temp messed up
the maid schedule again.

06:46.318 --> 06:47.842
Maybe it's time
to cut her loose.

06:47.885 --> 06:49.278
Him.

06:49.321 --> 06:50.801
Oh, sorry,
it's been three weeks.

06:50.845 --> 06:52.586
Let me catch you up.

06:52.629 --> 06:54.979
As you'll recall,
Petra had this temp.

06:55.023 --> 06:59.157
But then she had this one,
then this one and this one.

06:59.201 --> 07:00.637
And...

07:00.681 --> 07:02.073
But that's not the point.

07:02.117 --> 07:04.162
The point is
when I was cleaning,

07:04.206 --> 07:06.817
I found the engagement ring
I was going to give J.R.

07:06.861 --> 07:09.472
and I know I shouldn't have
looked at it, but I did,

07:09.516 --> 07:12.910
and now...
Aww.

07:15.522 --> 07:17.175
How long is this going to last?

07:17.219 --> 07:19.700
I'm so sick of crying.

07:19.743 --> 07:21.702
I feel like a Villanueva.

07:21.745 --> 07:24.792
I know, I know, but,

07:24.835 --> 07:27.098
uh, it's like I told you
on the phone last night...

07:27.142 --> 07:28.883
And the past 20 nights.

07:28.926 --> 07:30.667
...grieving is a process.

07:30.711 --> 07:33.104
Maybe it's time to take
the next step in the process.

07:33.148 --> 07:34.192
Showering?

07:34.236 --> 07:35.977
Returning the engagement ring.

07:36.020 --> 07:38.501
Will you come with me?Of course.
But tomorrow,

07:38.545 --> 07:40.024
'cause we're about
to have dinner.

07:41.112 --> 07:43.201
Did Alba make arepas?

07:43.245 --> 07:45.595
Yeah. Do you want to...Oh...

07:45.639 --> 07:47.945
Yeah, thanks.

07:53.951 --> 07:56.214
Geez, who died?

07:56.258 --> 07:59.087
Uh, actually, my mom's getting
her final PET scan tomorrow,

07:59.130 --> 08:01.611
to see if her cancer
treatment worked.

08:01.655 --> 08:02.873
PETRA:
Oh, my God,
I'm so sorry.

08:02.917 --> 08:04.788
I'll go.It's okay.

08:04.832 --> 08:07.095
Please stay.
ALBA: You're
just in time

08:07.138 --> 08:08.531
to pray with us.

08:08.575 --> 08:10.054
I will do it in English.

08:13.710 --> 08:17.018
We ask you, Heavenly Father,

08:17.061 --> 08:20.935
to guide Xiomara,
as you already have,

08:20.978 --> 08:24.242
through her journey with cancer.

08:24.286 --> 08:28.638
We pray that the treatments
have done their work,

08:28.682 --> 08:31.598
that her suffering is at an end.

08:31.641 --> 08:37.125
We pray that her life
from now on be blessed

08:37.168 --> 08:41.564
and full of joy and good health.

08:41.608 --> 08:45.786
In the name of the Father
and the Son

08:45.829 --> 08:49.093
and the Holy Spirit. Amen.Amen.

08:49.137 --> 08:51.313
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Amen.

08:58.233 --> 09:00.452
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
You'll recall,
we last left Jane

09:00.496 --> 09:01.976
praying for her mother.

09:02.019 --> 09:03.455
Her PET scan's later today.

09:03.499 --> 09:05.327
Waiting is the hardest part.

09:05.370 --> 09:09.853
Do you want to distract yourself
with some reading material?

09:09.897 --> 09:12.116
It is a real page-turner.Ooh.

09:12.160 --> 09:14.205
I especially love the part
about the color

09:14.249 --> 09:17.295
of the sunrise when you ran
Mateo to school last week.

09:17.339 --> 09:20.081
Okay, maybe my entries
are a little too detailed,

09:20.124 --> 09:21.691
but at least
you can read

09:21.735 --> 09:23.214
my handwriting. I...

09:23.258 --> 09:25.739
I am sorry,
but what is a "meldooper"?

09:25.782 --> 09:27.131
Meltdown.

09:27.175 --> 09:29.481
Oh. Oh, no, what happened?

09:29.525 --> 09:32.659
He lost it
at Ethan's birthday party.

09:32.702 --> 09:34.574
It was hard to sell him
on a nitrate-free Fruit Roll-Up

09:34.617 --> 09:36.140
when all the other kids
got cake.

09:36.184 --> 09:37.620
How bad?

09:37.664 --> 09:39.753
"We owe Ethan's mom
a new lamp" bad.

09:39.796 --> 09:41.319
It's not about the days...

09:41.363 --> 09:43.539
It's about the pattern. I know.

09:43.583 --> 09:45.323
It's just a small setback.

09:45.367 --> 09:47.151
Should we talk about it
over dinner?

09:47.195 --> 09:49.153
Oh, I, uh, can't tonight.

09:49.197 --> 09:51.112
What, you got a hot date?

09:51.155 --> 09:53.505
I mean, not a hotdate.

09:53.549 --> 09:55.943
Just a regular one?

09:55.986 --> 09:59.207
Careful.
Don't have a meldooper, Jane.

09:59.250 --> 10:02.558
Oh. Okay. Hope it goes well.

10:05.430 --> 10:07.955
Slow down, Mateo, you know
we don't run in the house.

10:07.998 --> 10:09.739
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
It's important to note

10:09.783 --> 10:12.742
that Jane wanted to talk
to herabuela about Rafael,

10:12.786 --> 10:15.658
but unfortunately,
she had bigger fish to fry.

10:17.399 --> 10:18.748
Do you?

10:18.792 --> 10:20.010
Hmm...

10:23.710 --> 10:24.928
Mm-hmm.

10:42.424 --> 10:45.645
If he can catch a giant fish,
I think he can probably

10:45.688 --> 10:47.647
make his own tuna sandwich.

10:52.260 --> 10:54.871
I know.
I'm-- I just mean,

10:54.915 --> 10:56.351
you're a strong,
independent

10:56.394 --> 10:59.789
woman. You don't have
to let him hang something

10:59.833 --> 11:01.269
on the wall
if you don't like it.

11:06.578 --> 11:08.493
And yours.

11:14.195 --> 11:16.414
Yeah, Jane. Ours.

11:16.458 --> 11:18.416
JANE:
It's like they're living
in the '50s.

11:18.460 --> 11:21.419
He might as well have said,
"Woman, go make me a sandwich!"

11:21.463 --> 11:23.334
Woman, go
easy on him.
Ah...

11:23.378 --> 11:26.120
I'm just worried this
will become a pattern.

11:26.163 --> 11:28.122
He's herhusband, not yours.

11:28.165 --> 11:30.167
And I know you don't excel
at minding your own business,

11:30.211 --> 11:33.605
but you should stay
out of their marriage.

11:33.649 --> 11:35.912
You've got this.

11:35.956 --> 11:37.522
Yeah?
Mm-hmm.

11:39.394 --> 11:41.396
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
And speaking of marriage...

11:41.439 --> 11:42.832
How did the
proposal go?

11:42.876 --> 11:44.834
Would I be standing here
with a ring if it went well?

11:45.922 --> 11:47.184
That was a rhetorical question.

11:47.228 --> 11:48.403
She just wants her money back.

11:48.446 --> 11:49.317
Right away.

11:51.972 --> 11:55.540
Wow.
Just handing over that ring

11:55.584 --> 11:57.586
makes me feel like
a weight has been lifted.

11:57.629 --> 11:59.501
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Well, it was
a three-carat diamond.

11:59.544 --> 12:01.111
You were right.

12:01.155 --> 12:03.418
Ooh, it feels good to get rid
of that reminder of J.R.

12:03.461 --> 12:06.769
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
That's one small step
for Petra...

12:06.813 --> 12:10.207
and one giant leap
for Rogelio de la Vega.

12:10.251 --> 12:12.427
That's right.
Dina really was on a roll.

12:12.470 --> 12:15.517
AndThis is Mars got a pilot
order from the network!

12:15.560 --> 12:17.432
How does that space suit feel?

12:17.475 --> 12:19.303
Sleek, supple
and slimming.

12:19.347 --> 12:22.524
I can't wait to get in front
of the cameras tomorrow.

12:22.567 --> 12:25.788
Rogelio, thank you for the
beautiful Martian bouquet.

12:25.832 --> 12:26.789
Of course.

12:33.361 --> 12:36.059
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Uh-oh. That's gonna
be a problem.

12:36.103 --> 12:37.669
They're not
gonna be a problem.

12:37.713 --> 12:39.497
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Oh, ignore me!

12:39.541 --> 12:41.325
We're so much more
talented than them.

12:41.369 --> 12:42.500
And you're so sexy.

12:42.544 --> 12:44.067
And you're
so gorgeous.

12:44.111 --> 12:46.243
And our skin glows
like the sun.

12:46.287 --> 12:49.725
BOTH:
And theirs will only get worse.

12:49.769 --> 12:51.553
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Looks like they have
a mantra, too.

12:53.511 --> 12:56.950
And so will your skin if
you keep frowning like that.

12:56.993 --> 12:58.560
Do you know
how much botox

12:58.603 --> 13:01.084
it takes to get rid
of worry wrinkles?

13:01.128 --> 13:04.000
Approximately eight
to 20 units.
Exactly.

13:04.044 --> 13:07.134
Forget them.

13:07.177 --> 13:08.962
No, I was just thinking
about Xiomara.

13:09.005 --> 13:12.792
She had her PET scan this
morning, so now we're waiting.

13:23.237 --> 13:26.936
It's just a telemarketer.

13:26.980 --> 13:29.809
Look, I appreciate the support,

13:29.852 --> 13:31.375
but you guys
should really go home.

13:31.419 --> 13:33.464
The doctor probably
won't even call today.

13:42.996 --> 13:44.649
Yeah.

13:44.693 --> 13:47.435
I thought I was headed in the
right direction, you know?

13:47.478 --> 13:49.176
Getting used to
us as friends.

13:49.219 --> 13:51.308
But this feels like
a real setback.

13:56.836 --> 13:59.186
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Yeah, remember, Jane,
you're gorgeous,

13:59.229 --> 14:00.796
your skin looks amazing, and--

14:00.840 --> 14:03.581
oh, sorry. Wrong mantra.

14:03.625 --> 14:05.148
"It's not about the days,

14:05.192 --> 14:08.586
it's about the pattern."

14:11.328 --> 14:12.590
It's the doctor's office.

14:12.634 --> 14:14.549
We're right here
with you, Mom.

14:15.942 --> 14:17.987
Mm-hmm.Thank you.

14:18.031 --> 14:19.467
But can I have
one of my hands back

14:19.510 --> 14:21.338
so I can answer?Oh!

14:26.039 --> 14:28.215
Hello?

14:28.258 --> 14:29.825
Yes, this is Xiomara.

14:31.566 --> 14:33.655
Okay.

14:35.787 --> 14:37.746
Okay.

14:37.789 --> 14:41.054
Thank you. Bye.

14:43.752 --> 14:46.233
I'm cancer-free.

14:46.276 --> 14:48.626
Oh, yes!

14:50.193 --> 14:53.588
Oh, I have to call your father.

14:53.631 --> 14:56.156
Oh, thank God.
I'm so happy.

14:56.199 --> 14:58.332
I can't wait to see you
tonight and celebrate.

14:58.375 --> 15:00.595
Okay. You too.

15:02.597 --> 15:06.122
Xo's PET scan results came
back, and she is cancer-free!

15:06.166 --> 15:08.211
Finally...

15:08.255 --> 15:10.561
we can be together!

15:10.605 --> 15:12.868
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Mars, we have a problem.

15:19.919 --> 15:21.659
Ms. Fields? They'd
like to see you

15:21.703 --> 15:24.140
for one more zero-
gravity hair test.

15:43.768 --> 15:45.814
To not having cancer.

15:45.857 --> 15:48.686
To not
having cancer.

15:52.038 --> 15:54.518
I've been saying it
over and over all day,

